Amendment to Partnership Agreement
This Amendment to the Partnership Agreement (the "Amendment") is made as of this 17 day of February,
2020, by and between 5 - Star Chiropractic Services, P.C., located at 56 Quarry Lane, Bedford, NY
10506 and Dr. Gary Stevens, located at 541 Main Street, Manasquan, NJ 08736 (each, a "Partner" and
collectively, the "Partners").
WHEREAS, the Partners formed a partnership under the name 5 - Star Chiropractic Services, P.C.
pursuant to a Partnership Agreement dated as of February 17, 2020, and any amendments thereto (the
"Partnership Agreement").
WHEREAS, the Partners now wish to amend certain provisions of the Partnership Agreement
pursuant to Section The performance of EMGs (electromyography) and NCVs (nerve conduction velocity)
of the Partnership Agreement.
NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and mutual covenants contained herein and
for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are acknowledged, the
Partners agree as follows:
1. This amendment, consisting of adding Dr. Gary Stevens as a partner with regards to the activity of
performing EMGs and NCVs ONLY, will contain five (5) provisions.
As the performance of the a fore-mentioned examinations will be performed by Dr. Stevens,
within offices that he alone attained, Dr. Stevens will be entitled to the largest percentage of the
reimbursed amount. Dr. Wattenmaker will serve as the manager and bookkeeper of said
accounts and will be compensated accordingly.
I)   If the performance of EMGs and/or NVCs are performed by Dr. Stevens within offices retained by
the efforts of Dr. Wattenmaker, both doctors will be entitled to 50% of the reimbursed amounts.
II)  Dr. Stevens, not the corporation of 5 – Star Chiropractic Services, P.C., shall be responsible for
the payment of his own workers compensation and disability insurance.
IV)  A quarterly reconciliation/accounting will be completed to ascertain the appropriate amount of
funds are withheld for quarterly payroll and taxes.
V)  Dr. Stevens will be provided a 1099 for his earnings to be settled with his own accountant for tax
purposes.
2. Capitalized terms used herein but not otherwise defined shall have the meaning ascribed to them in the
Partnership Agreement.
3. This Amendment may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which shall be deemed an
original and all of which together, shall constitute one and the same document.

ARTICLE V. MISCELLANEOUS PROVISIONS
5.01 Relationship of Parties. The relationship between the parties shall at all times be that of
Lessor and Lessee. No provision of this Agreement is intended, or shall be construed, to render
on Party an employee, contractor, or agent of the other Party. Lessee shall be responsible for,
and have exclusive control over, all aspects of the Services performed by the Lessee and its staff.
5.02 Arbitration. Any and all disputes, claims or causing of action involving, arising out of, or
related to, either directly or indirectly, this Agreement shall first be mediated between the Parties.
If mediation is unsuccessful, the dispute shall be submitted to arbitration, as the only method for
adjudicating them, before the American Arbitration Association in and for Bronx County, of
New York. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary, the arbitrator shall be empowered by the
Parties to attempt a mediated settlement of the matter prior to proceeding with the arbitration.
Each party may be represented by an attomey, each shall be responsible for its own attorneys
fees and other costs for the arbitration, and the Partics shall equally bear the cost of the arbitrator.
5.03 Effect of Invalidity; Change of Law. Should any part of this Agreement, for any reason,
be declared invalid, such decision shall not affect the validity of any remaining portion, which
remaining portion shall remain in force and effect as if this Agreement had been executed with
the invalid portion thereof eliminated, unless such construction would substantially frustrate the
purposes of the Parties for entering into this Agreement. In the event of any amendment, change
or modification (a "Change") to federal or state statutes, regulations, ordinances, rules or
policies, or the interpretation thereof by a court, by applicable governmental agencies or
authorities, or by legal counsel for either Party, which Change would in any manner prohibit,
restrict, limit or otherwise materially affect the ability of either Party to perform its duties and
obligations hereunder, or would materially affect the financial arrangements between the Partics
established by this Agreement, then the Parties shall negotiate promptly and in good faith to
amend this Agreement in response to such Change, and to maintain the arrangements between
the Parties established hereunder. In the event that such an amendment is not made effective by
the Parties within thirty (3) days following the effective date of the Change, this Agreement shall
terminate.
5.04 Non-Waiver. No waiver by either of the Parties of any failure by the other Party to keep or
perform any provision, covenant or condition of this Agreement shall be deemed a waiver of any
preceding or succeeding breach of the same, or of any other provision, covenant or condition.
All rights and remedies herein granted or referred to are cumulative, and resort to one shall not
preclude resort to another or any other right or remedy provided by law.
5.05 Successors and Assigns. All of the provisions herein contained shall be binding upon and
ensure to the benefit of the respective successors and permitted assigns of the Parties hereto, to
the same extent as if such successors and assigns were in each case names as a Party to this
